03:36.000 --> 03:39.000
The bedrock of this type of comic tends to feature several characters,

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
often representative of the authors,

03:41.000 --> 03:43.000
sitting on a couch making hilarious jokes

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
about video games that are out right now

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
or inside the fiction of a video game

03:47.000 --> 03:49.000
interacting with it to hilarious consequences.

03:49.000 --> 03:51.000
These two forms were the bedrock

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
of many early gaming webcomics

03:53.000 --> 03:55.000
from the late 90s to the early 2000s,

03:55.000 --> 03:57.000
and there were many successful comics using this format

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
like Penny Arcade, PvP, Little Gamers,

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
Bob & George, 8-Bit Theater, and others.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
